  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Editorial Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Produce engaging content for various mediums including publications, blog posts, videos, photo stories, etc;</li>\n  <li>Manage clients' projects and maintain good communications;</li>\n  <li>Editing &amp; Proofreading of relevant content to ensure quality work</li>\n  <li>Execute assigned duties to meet the objectives of overall communications strategy.<br>\nDrive content updates to build a strong digital presence for the organisation</li>\n  <li>Monitor the online and more specifically, social media space, for relevant news, comments and feedback.</li>\n  <li>Responsible for administrative support duties related to marketing and content and other projects where applicable.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>At least a Diploma in Mass Communications, English Language, Journalism, Public Relations, or a related discipline.</li>\n  <li>At least 1 years of experience in a similar role.</li>\n  <li>Strong interpersonal relationship skills who can work in a team and also work well independently.</li>\n  <li>Organised and meticulous, strong in admin functions</li>\n  <li>Excellent oral and written communications skills</li>\n  <li>A proven and successful track record</li>\n  <li>Tech savvy and up to date with social media trends, platforms and best practices<br>\nPhotoshop, Illustrator and InDesign skills and knowledge.</li>\n</ul>",
